				<h2 class="title icon icon0">
					Re: Just got refused disability welfare, again
				</h2>
				

						
						
							
						
				<div class="content ">
					<div id="post_message_1786874">
						<blockquote class="postcontent restore ">
							Backster<br />
no, the government's idea was that because housing benefit was getting so expensive, they'd curtail it...<br />
<br />
who list of things all smashing into each other like a train wreck form hell<br />
<br />
Maggie Thatcher wanted working class people to turn into Tories, so she started a scheme that let council house renters, to buy the properties they lived in at a discount<br />
BUT, without using the money raised to build new properties!<br />
And it was to make the bankers rich as sin, setting off the housing boom, but getting people into massive debt, as the boom ramped up, house prices greatly exceeded their true worth, 3 or 4 times true value in Southern England was common, hence, infamously a large cupboard, I shit thee not a cupboard, was sold off as a bedroom in London for £40,000<br />
<br />
now, consequences of that were enormous. Since folk on low pay or welfare got housing benefit to help let them be able to afford homes, the cost of welfare went up, some were even forced ot live in Bed &amp; breakfast places as there wasn't enough houses and local councils picking up the tab.<br />
<br />
in reality 2/3rds of council homes ended up in the hands of private landlords, who pushed the rents up...dunno if Americans have ever heard of the term &quot;Rachmanism&quot;, a term coined form an infamous, abusive landlord in the 1960s, well he was nothing compared to what came later.<br />
<a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Peter_Rachman" target="_blank" rel="nofollow">http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Peter_Rachman</a><br />
<br />
Very very few council houses were ever built with 1 room, 2 or 3 being the norm. So, how will all these people like me, get a house?<br />
And WHY THE FUCK SHOULD I MOVE FORM THE HOME I HAVE LIVED IN FOR 28 YEARS? it's very very far form being in a desirable high rent area, FFS :P<br />
<br />
This crap has caused effective &quot;ethnic cleansing&quot; of the poor from areas in London etc, speculators take the land over, sell flats that go for £800,000 etc causing a knock on spiral on the locale' and so, &quot;essential workers&quot; etc are having to travel further and further to commute if London  wants workers.<br />
<br />
meanwhile, of course, our &quot;Front Bench&quot; MPs (Cabinet) get two houses paid for them and lots and lots of nice freebies like trying to remember is it 4 restaurants and 9 bars? in houses of Parliament with massive subsidies.<br />
<br />
on top of many other things that are going on, frankly the hatred is exceeding that for Thatcher and the damage is soon going to exceed hers, socially. only the improvements in ten+ years the Tories were kicked out, have set up a &quot;cushion&quot;, when that wears out frankly,, piss on the government and the corporates/elite. Poll Tax Riots are gonna be small potatoes and as commentators are now admitting, the riots other year were about social outrage
						</blockquote>
					</div>

					
				</div>
			</div>
			
